      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:124:4",
      "text": [
        " الْكِبْرُ رِدَاءُ اللَّهِ وَ الْمُتَكَبِّرُ يُنَازِعُ اللَّهَ رِدَاءَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Ibn Fazzal, from Sa’alba, from Mo’mar Bin Umar Bin Ata’a, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The Pride is a Gown of Allah<sup>azwj</sup> and the arrogant one disputes Allah<sup>azwj</sup> about His<sup>azwj</sup> Gown’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. Abu Ali al-Ash’ari has narrated from Muhammad ibn ‘Abd al-Jabbar from ibn Faddal from Tha’labah from Mu’ammar ibn ‘Umar ibn ‘Ata’ from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “Pride is the gown of Allah. An arrogant person (assuming arrogance) disputes Allah about His gown.” "
        ]
      }
    },
